about.summary: Fitting a principal curve to a data matrix in arbitrary dimensions.  Hastie and Stuetzle (1989) <doi:10.2307/2289936>.

name: r-princurve
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '2.1.4' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-princurve
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/princurve_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/princurve/princurve_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f25e9b956152e4446f8918a0813d8f6dc1df381d97cf89ab7693233154ce6fac

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 3
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('princurve')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('princurve')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/rcannood/princurve
  license: GPL-2
  summary: Fitting a principal curve to a data matrix in arbitrary dimensions.  Hastie and Stuetzle
    (1989) <doi:10.2307/2289936>.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - MathiasHaudgaard
    - FrodePedersen
    - ArneKr
